## Sensor Geometry

### Pen Frame Convention
```
+X = right, real world west
+Y = forward, Real world south(away from you when writing)
+Z = up towards the sky.
```

### Sensor Positions
```
S1: (0,    +1.0, +1.3) cm  [behind magnet]
S2: (-1.2,  0,   +1.3) cm  [right of magnet]
S3: ~13.5cm up pen barrel    [far from ball, reads Earth field only]
```

### Sensor Axis Orientations
```
S1:  sensor_x = pen -x
     sensor_y = pen +Z
     sensor_z = pen +y

S2:  sensor_x = pen -Y
     sensor_y = pen +Z
     sensor_z = pen -X

MPU6050 (accel + gyro):
     sensor_x = pen -Z
     sensor_y = pen +Y
     sensor_z = pen +X

S3 compass (MMC5603, X axis inverted):
     sensor_x = pen -Y
     sensor_y = pen +X
     sensor_z = pen +Z
```

### Rotation Matrices (raw → pen frame: B_pen = R.T @ raw)
```python
R_S1 = np.array([[ 1,  0,  0],
                 [ 0,  0,  1],
                 [ 0, -1,  0]])

R_S2 = np.array([[ 0,  1,  0],
                 [ 0,  0,  1],
                 [ 1,  0,  0]])

R_acc = np.array([[ 0,  0, -1],
                  [ 0,  1,  0],
                  [ 1,  0,  0]])
# IMPORTANT: gravity = -R_acc.T @ raw  (must negate)

R_gyro = R_acc  # same chip, same orientation

R_compass = np.array([[ 0, -1,  0],
                      [ 1,  0,  0],
                      [ 0,  0, -1]])
```

