## Key Physics Discoveries

### 1. Blind Spot
```
rv = cross(m_prev, m_curr)
|rv| = dα × sin(θ)

When θ = 0 (dipole aligns with rotation axis):
  sin(0) = 0 → signal disappears
  This is physical — the magnetic field literally does not change
  No number of magnetometers can fix this
  Only a quadrupole magnet or gyroscope can cover it
  In practice: rare and brief during normal writing
```

### 2. Cross Product is Already Spin-Free
```
rv = cross(m_prev, m_curr) is ALWAYS perpendicular to m_prev
Spin removal via m_neutral subtraction = mathematical no-op
No spin removal code needed
```

### 3. Direction Ambiguity
```
rv direction depends on current dipole orientation
Same physical forward roll → different rv direction
as dipole drifts over time
Fix: project rv onto horizontal plane using gravity,
     then onto compass-defined North/East axes
```

### 4. MMC5603 vs BMM150
```
MMC5603: SET/RESET technique → rejects 50Hz AC interference ✓
BMM150:  Hall effect, no SET/RESET → 50Hz noise corrupts readings ✗
Use MMC5603 for compass — BMM150 unusable in normal environments
```

### 5. Small Angle Approximation
```
At 500Hz sampling: rotation per frame ≈ 1° = 0.017 rad
sin(0.017) = 0.017000 (exact)
Error = 0.00001% → completely negligible
Justifies treating |rv| ≈ rotation angle directly
```

